<title><![CDATA[Sr. Marketing Analyst]]></title>
<trackingCode><![CDATA[625-702]]></trackingCode>
<jobDescription><![CDATA[<p><strong>Summary of Responsibilities:</strong></p>
<p><strong> </strong></p>
<p>The Business Development Analyst will be responsible for supporting the business development team and business development management within the department. The BD Analyst will help management assess, develop, and facilitate programs and initiatives within the business development department. The Business Development Analyst reports to either the Business Development Director or SVP.</p>
<p> </p>
<p><strong>Essential Functions:</strong></p>
<p><strong> </strong></p>
<ul>
<li>This is a highly autonomous role  where the incumbent must possess the ability to be self-sufficient.</li>
<li>Identify, evaluate and implement  strategies to improve conversion rates within the direct-to-consumer  businesses</li>
<li>Keep up-to-date with industry trends and competitor products.  Make recommendations to improve existing  product functionality. </li>
<li>Create, oversee, and maintain reports to measure product performance. Create monthly statistic dashboard and use historical data to analyze and make recommendations.</li>
<li>Either possesses or has the  ability to quickly grasp ecommerce, including Sitecore and associated  reporting.</li>
<li>Implement strategic  business plans for assigned accounts that will deliver maximum potential  volume and profitability.  Plan activities that directly support the implementation of efforts to grow volume, profitability, market share.</li>
<li>Act as a   technical liaison with IT and Business Operations to ensure   that any new systems or IT changes are ‘field ready’ before launch</li>
<li>Supports new  partner launches, training.</li>
<li>Interface with  internal departments to coordinate systems and reporting for all field activities</li>
<li>Work with IT, Marketing and Sales Trainer on updates, analysis and training account executives on  utilization of technology based systems</li>
<li>Help connect internal organizations that need field input to get what they need without  undue sales disruption</li>
</ul>
<ul>
<li>Work with internal teams including: Compliance, Legal, IT, Funding, Credit and  Business Development to coordinate projects that involve Direct businesses      systems</li>
<li>Work with Sales  Force on email campaigns</li>
<li>Help Marketing  to manage campaigns via SalesForce</li>
</ul>
<p><strong>Other Functions:</strong></p>
<p><strong> </strong></p>
<ul>
<li>Assists with Direct-to-Consumer (HelpingLoans, Roadloans) Partner training and support</li>
<li>Special projects as requested</li>
<li>Performs other duties as assigned</li>
</ul>]]></jobDescription>
<requiredSkills><![CDATA[<p><strong>Requirements:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>Bachelor’s degree in a technical discipline required, although equivalent combination of education and experience may be substituted in lieu of degree; master’s preferred.</li>
<li>Ability to work both independently and collaboratively with other team members delivering quality projects with aggressive timelines.</li>
<li>Strong working knowledge of SQL.</li>
<li>Strong preference to have a undergraduate finance degree</li>
<li>Five years of experience working in some kind of analytical capacity.  Needs the ability to utilize a analytical approach to problem solving, business case review, market research.</li>
<li>Knowledge of SilverPop and Direct Mail/Marketing campaigns a plus.</li>
</ul>
<ul>
<li>Exceptional  analytical skills and superior Microsoft Excel and other analytical  packages; experience with SQL or other related development languages</li>
<li>Five (5) + years of experience working with internal clients to deliver complex  solutions that impact business operations</li>
</ul>
<ul>
<li>Strong  project management, communication and negotiation skills.</li>
<li>Excellent  interpersonal, written and verbal communication skills.</li>
<li>Ability  to manage multiple projects and effectively meet deadlines.</li>
<li>Knowledge  of testing and performance characterization process</li>
<li>Other:   .NET, HTML</li>
<li>Ability   to maintain confidentiality.</li>
</ul>
<p> </p>
<p> </p>
<p><strong>Working Conditions:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>Extended  work hours may be required as dictated by management and business needs.</li>
<li>Travel  to multiple facilities may be required.</li>
<li>May be required to lift, push, or pull materials weighing up to twenty (20)  pounds.</li>
</ul>
<ul>
<li>May be required to sit and review information on a computer screen for long periods of time.</li>
<li>May require repetitive motions of the hands and wrist related to writing and typing at an electronic keyboard.</li>
<li>Corporate / satellite office role.</li>
</ul>]]></requiredSkills>
